business.name: Fun With Kids Wellbeing Family Day Care Centre
business.tagline: A warm, safe and nurturing family day care where children learn at their own pace.
business.description:
At Fun With Kids Wellbeing Family Day Care Centre we believe all children are unique and need a warm, safe, secure, nurturing and friendly environment where they can learn at their own pace.

We provide an educational and balanced program that aims to reflect the social and cultural identity of every child attending the centre. We believe play is the primary way in which children learn and we foster this approach by providing stimulating, enjoyable and varied learning experiences for all age groups.

Fun With Kids is registered with Beaucare Family Day Care scheme, which has been operating since April 1993. We are a licenced and approved service and as such must meet all requirements of the Government.

about.heading: About Rachel
about.story: Rachel has over 30 years of early childhood teaching experience and has operated with Beaucare Family Day Care since 1993.
about.philosophy: Every child is unique. The care model is holistic and play-based, supporting social, emotional and developmental growth in a secure, family-like environment.

reviews.author: Nikita Pienaar
reviews.text:
On searching for a daycare for my baby, I was so overwhelmed by the ‚Äòbig daycare centers‚Äô and how they would ever have time for my little man and his needs.

I‚Äôm so grateful to have found Rachel and Fun with kids. Rachel loves all the kids, and works with them to provide a tailored approach. It feels like I‚Äôm leaving my baby with family. The Centre is loving, well equipped and Rachel provides the best care and environment I could ask for.

reviews.author: Maria W
reviews.text:
We came across from a large daycare organisation  to Rachels fun with kids well-being family daycare and it has been the best decision we ever made.
We were battling constant sickness every week, and it is now such a relief to see our little princess happy, healthy and thriving.
Rachel has such a deep and loving connection with the children and provides a supportive, safe and nurturing environment.
Rachel is a great communicator and is always happy to discuss about the events of the day.
It‚Äôs wonderful to receive updates, photos and videos of the children on how they learn, explore and grow in their development.
I would happily recommend to any parent that is looking for a caring, professional, fun and educational environment for their children.
It is our daughters home away from home.
Thank-you Rachel, your a star ‚≠êÔ∏è

reviews.author: Priyanka Kumar
reviews.text: What can I say about Rachel she is one beautiful lady who is loving, caring and very positive talking lady. My son who had separation anxiety and we tried two different daycare before and all I hear is negative comments from educator which makes me very depressed even though i told them about it earlier about his situation. And I hated the pick ups. But Rachel she is very motivating not just to children but to parents as well. And my son who is so happy with her and the ways she treats him. She is easy to communicate and work as a team for our sons wellbeing instead of pressurising me.  I am one happy mumma. we are so Blessed to have her.

reviews.author: Amber Day
reviews.text:
First and foremost I could not thank you and the way you are with our children enough.  It is a true testament to you and the environment in which you hold so dearly and proudly at Fun With Kids.  You have raised two of my children in the most nurturing, characteristic, emotionally sensitive and grounding ways that our children are a true reflection of the skills, knowledge and insight you have portrayed upon them.  We were recommended to you by a colleague/friend and couldn‚Äôt thank her enough for sharing her hidden ‚ÄòGem‚Äô (Rachel) with us.  We consider you and your husband surrogate grandparents to our children.  You are focussed, fair and allow our children to tap into their independency and provide the necessary skills for my son and my daughter to hone in on their natural born abilities.

You have created a very educational, fun, thought provoking indoor and outdoor area in which the children feel very safe and free to move about and experience each and every stimulating idea they have in each of the corners through sensory play.  It is from my observation over the 3 years of your services that there is not one space the children cannot access nor a draw or cupboard that is not full with the adventures of life that every kid wants to do at home and cant. The philosophy you have created behind the scenes for Fun With Kids is from the heart.

We could not recommend you enough to help raise our children ‚Äì we just love Fun With Kids!

reviews.author: Jessica Prichard
reviews.text:
I feel very blessed to have found Rachel‚Äôs daycare and there be a vacancy for my 2yr old son. I had been looking for a long time for the perfect place and I kept coming back to Rachel‚Äôs website and was happy to go on the waiting list. But I was thrilled when I was offered a day right away.

Jake had never been to care before so I was a bit concerned as to how he would go but he absolutely loved it and didn‚Äôt want to leave.

Rachel made both of us feel very welcomed and like part of the family right away and I knew I had made the right decision for care for Jake.

Rachel‚Äôs place is the ideal place for young children with so many activities and things to do. I especially love her outdoor area and can see how much fun her kids have there everyday.

Rachel is also a great communicator and filled me in on how my son was going and sent photos and videos of him throughout the day showing how much fun they were having.

I feel very confident to leave my son with Rachel and I only hope more days become available for me to send him there for more fun throughout the week.

Thank you Rachel for making this experience so easy for us and for caring for my boy so well.

reviews.author: Maddi Orourke
reviews.text: Racheal is amazing! I‚Äôm so lucky to be able to send Harvey to her family daycare, his never been to any daycares before this and I‚Äôm so happy with the environment and professionalism that the centre holds. Harvey is always so happy when arriving to be picked up and feel so comfortable leaving him with Racheal. Super super grateful for all she does for him and the activities and teaching she is providing. She loves him as her own. Couldn‚Äôt recommend the centre more! LOVE LOVE LOVE

reviews.author: Alice Anderson
reviews.text: Both my children have attended Rachel‚Äôs centre, she is incredibly nurturing and provides the best environment for all her kids on a daily basis. They are never without a fun activity and Rachel‚Äôs constant guidance to oversee their progression and learning. She has a passion for early childhood development and does not treat her daily tasks like a job, rather it is her mission to work with the parents in bringing out each child‚Äôs unique qualities whilst also ensuring their overall development and adjustment to the world. I cannot recommend Rachel enough for your babies and toddlers!

reviews.author: Melissa Hays
reviews.text:
Rachel is an amazing family day care educator. Some of the reasons why I think she is the best educator are as follows:
- She loves and cares for each and every child like they are her own
- She focuses on providing a safe and supportive environment for the children to thrive
- She encourages the children and supports their learning through singing songs, music, different craft activities, gardening and encouraging independent play
- She goes above and beyond with giving the parents 'love letters' at the end of each day outlining how the day has been and things they have done/learnt
My child loves Rachel so much that he does not want to come home!

reviews.author: Chenoa Daley
reviews.text: Rachel creates a warm, loving and creative environment for our previous children with the most amazing facilities where children can run and play in her large backyard, spacious indoor play area, and everything is clean and in excellent condition. Rachel cared for both my children over a 5 year period and I was so pleased to have found her she genuinely impacted my whole family.

reviews.author: Kezia Dover
reviews.text: Rachel is a wonderful educator. She creates a warm and comforting environment which allows my daughter to feel comfortable to go and stay in her care. Rachel creates fun filled activities for the kids allowing them to use their imagination and also develop independence and confidence.

reviews.author: Katy Pearse
reviews.text:
We are so fortunate to have found Fun With Kids. Rachel currently cares for our daughter and I highly recommend her. Rachel provides learning experiences for all age groups and allows the children to lead the learning by observing their individual interests and needs.
Fun With Kids is more than just a day care centre, it is a warm and loving home where children feel very welcome, loved and safe. Rachel is definitely the safe pair of hands you want looking after your child.

posts.summary:
At our Enchanted Garden our children immersed with nature. We have birds visiting us each day. Outside we have many opportunities for exploring and leaning. Our giant Poinciana tree gives beautiful shade over our cubby house. On a rainy day, we welcomed a visitor ‚Äì a kookaburra. Our special bike path provides  so many fun and exciting challenges for our little ones. They love running, push bikes, chasing each other and using the grass as their park.
Delightful play at our garden!

posts.title: Hi, my name is Rachel Holmes. I am an accredited Early Childhood Teacher and Edu
posts.summary:
Hi, my name is Rachel Holmes. I am an accredited Early Childhood Teacher and Educator who operates 'Fun with Kids' wellbeing Family Daycare Centre at The Observatory in Reedy Creek, Gold Coast. 
After many years working in the early childhood industry I have developed a concept by creating an optimum, intimate and warm environment with an ongoing holistic approach (physical, mental, emotional and spiritual-moral) to raise our precious beautiful babies and toddlers. I call it a "boutique incubator", just like baby chicks bursting out of their shells and ready to grow ha!
I believe all children are unique and need a warm, safe, secure, nurturing and friendly environment where they can learn at their own pace. I provide an educational and balanced program that aims to reflect the social and cultural identity of every child attending my centre. I believe play is the primary way in which children learn and I will foster this approach by providing stimulating, enjoyable and varied learning experiences. I allow children to learn through their interests, decision making and collaboration with others, whilst focussing on their strengths and building on their emerging skills base (affiliated with the Montessori philosophy). 
As a family day care educator, I also recognise the importance of strong partnerships with children and their families. 
'Fun With Kids Wellbeing FDC Centre' is registered, licenced and an 'approved service' and as such must meet all requirements of the Government.
